&lt;p&gt;StepStone Private Debt (SPD) is a global private debt investor with over $87B in AUM/AUA including $12B based on the latest Q2 firm figures. SPD covers the breadth of the private debt market and constructs bespoke portfolios on a primary, secondary and co-investment basis. SPD focuses on two areas of the market: performing and non-performing debt across the corporate, real estate, and infrastructure sectors. SPD is a subsidiary of the StepStone Group, a global private markets firm specializing in Private Equity, Infrastructure, Private Credit and Real Estate.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;StepStone Private Debt is seeking a detail-oriented individual to join the team and provide comprehensive support across multiple business functions. This role offers exposure to senior professionals in areas such as research and investment, legal and compliance, monitoring and reporting, operations, and sales. The intern will contribute to presenting Private Debt’s service offerings and investment products to institutional investors, assist with client servicing, and support internal processes that drive efficiency and growth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The person should have a solid understanding of investments and private markets, strong project management and writing skills. Understanding of business development and capital raising processes is also desired.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide support to the Client Solutions team on project management, client servicing, and portfolio related tasks and analysis as required.
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in the preparation, updating, and optimisation of presentations, pitch decks, and marketing materials.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the creation, maintenance, and accuracy of databases, reports, and case studies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist portfolio managers and team members with portfolio analysis, monitoring, and performance reviews.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to the development and updating of internal and external communications and documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in ad hoc projects and&amp;nbsp;analyses across business functions (e.g., investments, operations, reporting).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide administrative support for planning, data entry, and project coordination.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with multiple teams to ensure consistent messaging and up-to-date information.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Undertake other duties as assigned to support the needs of the business.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What we’re looking for&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s degree required, concentration in finance, business administration, economics, or equivalent preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fluency in English is required, German is a strong plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must be able to commit 12 months&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Highly motivated individual with demonstrated initiative, independence and adaptability&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in Excel, Powerpoint, Word and other Microsoft office programs&lt;/li&gt;
