&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-teams=&quot;true&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;ui-provider a b c d e f g h i j k l m n o p q r s t u v w x y z ab ac ae af ag ah ai aj ak&quot;&gt;We are global private markets specialists&amp;nbsp;delivering tailored investment solutions,&amp;nbsp;advisory services, and impactful, data driven&amp;nbsp;insights to the world’s investors.&amp;nbsp;Leveraging the power of our platform and&amp;nbsp;our peerless intelligence across sectors,&amp;nbsp;strategies, and geographies, we help&amp;nbsp;identify the advantages and the answers&amp;nbsp;our clients need to succeed.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h4&gt;Position Overview&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Data Operations Junior Analyst will work for a team that supports the Portfolio Analytics &amp;amp; Reporting (“SPAR”), Investor Relations, and Fund Accounting teams in collecting and managing data and the flow of documents for numerous private market investments.&amp;nbsp;40 hours per week opportunity for a 16-week period with the possibility to extend or to transition to a permanent career opportunity with StepStone.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Essential Job Functions:&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintaining the StepStone Reporting Inbox by processing all emails received daily, gathering associated information from third party providers (including APIs); and creating and storing electronic files of all data received&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attending to document escalation requests on the SPAR Internal Signals list and resolving missing document inquiries in a timely manner&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Providing strict and timely follow-up on all communications and adhering to SPAR department procedures&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Reviewing numerous electronic documents and adhering to a precise file naming convention system&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Resolve untagged documents in accordance with risk control SOP’s&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assisting with the management of client SharePoint sites by uploading documents and responding to client inquiries and requests&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinating with fellow team members around the globe to meet SPAR mission objectives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assisting the overall SPAR team on expanded scope projects and tasks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Education and/or Work Experience Requirements:&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in accounting, economics, finance, or business preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated track record of academic success&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prior private equity, investment banking, planning and analysis, or research experience a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Required Knowledge, Skills and Abilities&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong organizational skills and the ability to multi-task and manage time in a detail-oriented environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong Excel skills and familiarity with the Microsoft Office Suite&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience using Microsoft Power BI, Microsoft Power Automate and Microsoft SharePoint a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Follow up skills and acute attention to accuracy and detail are essential&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Highly motivated individual with demonstrated initiative, independence, and adaptability&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fluent in English both written and spoken&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
